In [9]:
# aggregate by country
country_df = df_raw.groupby('Country/Region', as_index=False).sum() 
country_df.drop(columns=['Lat', 'Long'], inplace=True)

# Transpose the dataframe
country_df = pd.DataFrame(country_df.T)
country_df.columns = country_df.iloc[0,:]
country_df.drop(index='Country/Region', inplace=True)

# Get the five countries that have the most cases on the most recent available date
top_countries = country_df.sort_values(by=country_df.index[-1], axis=1, ascending=False).iloc[:,:20]
In [12]:
fig = go.Figure()

for country in top_countries.columns:
    fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=top_countries.index, y=top_countries[country], mode='lines', name=country))

fig.update_layout(title={'text':'Cumulative Cases by Country','y':0.95,'x':0.5},
                   xaxis_title='Date',
                   yaxis_title='No. of Cases')

fig.show()

                   xaxis_title='Date',
                   yaxis_title='No. of Cases')

# Static Plot of Cases on March 23
colors = ["#000004","crimson","lightseagreen","orange"]
limits = [(0,3),(4,10),(11,20),(21,180)]
scale = 1500

fig = go.Figure()

for i in range(len(limits)):
    lim = limits[i]
    df_sub = df_new[lim[0]:lim[1]]
    fig.add_trace(go.Scattergeo(locationmode = 'country names',
                                locations = df_sub['Country/Region'],
                                marker = dict(size = df_sub.iloc[:,-1]/scale,
                                              color = colors[i],
                                              line_color = 'rgb(40,40,40)',
                                              line_width = 0.5,
                                              sizemode = 'area'),
                                name = 'Rankings {0}-{1}'.format(lim[0],lim[1])))

fig.update_layout(title = {'text':'No. of Cases Worldwide','y':0.95,'x':0.5}, 
                  showlegend = True, 
                  geo = dict(scope = 'world',
                            landcolor = 'rgb(217, 217, 217)',
                            showland = True,
                            showcountries = True))

fig.show()

# Data manipulation for easier plotting
df_stacked = pd.DataFrame(df_new.set_index('Country/Region').stack(), columns=['Number'])
df_stacked.reset_index(inplace=True)
df_stacked.rename(columns={'level_1':'Date'}, inplace=True)
df_stacked.Number = df_stacked.Number.astype('int')
In [32]:
# Geoplot with Animation
fig = px.scatter_geo(df_stacked, 
                     locations="Country/Region",
                     locationmode = 'country names',
                     hover_name="Country/Region", 
                     size="Number",
                     animation_frame="Date",
                     projection="equirectangular",)

fig.update_layout(title = {'text':'No. of Cases Time-Lapse<br>'\
                           '(Drage to See Across Different Dates)','y':0.95,'x':0.5},
                 geo = dict(showcountries=True))
fig.show()
